[Surgical treatment of far-advanced gastric cancer].

[Article in Japanese]

Okajima K, Yamada S.

Surgical treatment of far-advanced gastric cancer should be categorized as part 
of a multidisciplinary treatment. Its therapeutic principles may be summarized 
as follows: survival should be expected; operative death must be avoided; any 
operation promoting the growth of cancer should be avoided; oral intake should 
be made possible, pain should be eased; and the main focus must be removed as 
far as possible. In the cases with positive peritoneal dissemination, even at 
