Palliative intubation in malignant stricture of the oesophagus and cardia.

Fjøsne HE, Erichsen HG, Sanderud A, Myrvold HE.

One-hundred patients treated with oesophageal intubation for stricture-forming 
inoperable oesophago-gastric malignancies during the years 1972 to 1983 were 
analyzed. Fifteen tubes were endoscopically positioned, the rest by thoracotomy 
or laparotomy. Seven patients died from causes related to the intubation, the 
causes of death being perforation (2), mediastinitis (3) or aortic erosion (2). 
