170. Surg Gynecol Obstet. 1987 Aug;165(2):111-5.

The reversed gastric esophagoplasty in palliation of carcinoma of the esophagus.

Giraud RM, Berzin S.

The reversed whole stomach was used in 29 patients to bypass nonresectable 
carcinoma of the esophagus. The mobilized distal stomach, after duodenal 
transection immediately beyond the pylorus, was placed in a substernal and 
anterior mediastinal tunnel and the prepyloric area was anastomosed to the 
